programme.title: Ika-6 Na Utos
إكا-6 نا أوتوس
programme.desc: The story of a married couple where the husband is having an extra marital affair and will leave his loyal, caring and chubby wife for his seductive mistress. جي أم إيه بينوي تي هي قناة ترفيه على مدار الساعة طوال الأسبوع حيث تتضمن مسلسلات حديثة، كوميدية، حوارية، واقعية، مسلية ومتنوعة فضلاً عن برامج إخبارية من قناة جي أم إيه في الفيليبين. باللغتين الإنكليزية والفيليبينية

The last time we saw crime-solving crack team Brennan and Booth, the forensic anthropologist stunned her FBI partner with news that she was pregnant with his child. Entering season seven, we pick up with the pair, well into Brennan's pregnancy, as they adjust to their new life as an expectant couple and deal with the forthcoming changes. Still seeing the world from radically different perspectives, Brennan and Booth will also continue to deal with a series of gruesome and baffling crimes

programme.title: Bones

programme.title: Hawaii Five-0

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Bottomless. In a case inspired by a true-life incident, a shady businessman becomes the chief suspect in the murder of a young lawyer

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Driven. The daddy of the crime drama genre displays its pedigree with a racially-charged and engaging episode. Green (Jesse L Martin) and Lupo (Jeremy Sisto) are thrown into the thick of the action when a white teenager and a young black girl are shot dead. The investigation threatens to collapse before it's even begun when the locals remain tight-lipped about events that may have triggered the tragedy, but the detectives refuse to back down. Their dogged determination pays off when they discover that one of the victims had been involved in an altercation with a neighbour. Will this lead prove fruitful?

programme.title: Law & Order
programme.desc: Political Animal. Blood continues to spill on the mean streets of New York. Green (Jesse L Martin) and Lupo (Jeremy Sisto) are tested by a triple homicide, which they initially decide is the grisly result of a lovers' quarrel. As ever, appearances are deceiving and nothing is as it first seems. On closer inspection, the detectives uncover a link to a conman with political connections

programme.title: Think Like a Man
programme.desc: This adaptation of Steve Harvey's non-fiction relationship advice book Act Like a Lady, Think Like a Man focuses on six friends who regularly get together to play basketball, and usually are commiserating about women issues. Jeremy (Jerry Ferrara) is a geeky pothead and comic-book obsessive whose career is stuck in neutral and who won't pop the question to his girlfriend of nine years. Zeke (Romany Malco) is a former musician-turned-businessman who is great at picking up the ladies but can't commit to a long-term relationship. Michael (Terrence J) is good looking and charming, but his mother still has him wrapped around her finger and doesn't want to let him go. Dominic (Michael Ealy) keeps changing career goals, and while he's an excellent chef, he hasn't found a way to make it pay. And short, motormouthed Cedric (Kevin Hart) is in the midst of a divorce and can't wait to be free of his wife. Nerdy but well-meaning Bennett (Gary Owen) is the only one in a functioning relationship, and he gets a lot of grief from his buddies for his happy marriage
